{"node_id": "e29d81", "title": "Minimize tool sets", "path": "subagents > Subagents > Best practices > Minimize tool sets", "content": "Only give subagents the tools they need. This improves focus and security:\n\n```python  theme={null}\n# ✅ Good: Focused tool set\nemail_agent = {\n    \"name\": \"email-sender\",\n    \"tools\": [send_email, validate_email],  # Only email-related\n}\n\n# ❌ Bad: Too many tools\nemail_agent = {\n    \"name\": \"email-sender\",\n    \"tools\": [send_email, web_search, database_query, file_upload],  # Unfocused\n}\n```", "summary": "Discusses the importance of providing subagents with only necessary tools to enhance focus and security.", "keywords": ["subagents", "tool sets", "security", "focus", "email_agent", "send_email", "validate_email"]}